{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a22a6cd-9877-41fb-a65c-f46a7b1ab7b6","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then run:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore   # restore packages for the new TFM\ndotnet build     # verify it compiles\ndotnet test      # run tests if applicable\n```\n\n**Watch out for:**\n- NuGet packages that don't yet support `net11.0` — check for updated versions.\n- Any TFM-conditional code (`#if NET10_0`) that may need a `NET11_0` branch.\n- Breaking API changes listed in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"39c87c1d-dc8b-494a-8e1d-054dde70c2d4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":362,"requestId":"681E:BF033:2676D3E:2A6B2D8:69FD29E8"},"id":"b3bec3b2-74ac-4399-8e9d-8ac15de2b850","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:10:23.424Z","parentId":"4eb52be4-d7fe-4f21-aa5a-31f074960c72"}
